# Exercise 005 - Build, deploy, and expose a php application via S2I

1) Create a new project name "s2i-test" and deploy a new app based on a simple
   php repository (i.e. https://github.com/jtdagmaj/PHP_helloworld);

2) Check if a BuildConfig was fired by the DeploymentConfig and follow its
   output;

3) After the build, check if a Pod was correctly scheduled and a Service was
   created;

4) Expose the Service and retrieve the exposed url;

5) Try accessing it with a browser;

BONUS) Export the "php" image stream definition related to the openshift
       project and check its contents;
